Government Circular-
With regard to the effective implementation of the Maharashtra Right to Public Service Act, 2015, Shri. The Chief Commissioner,
Notified Services under Housing Department at a meeting chaired by the State Right to Service Commission.
It has been directed to appoint a study group of experts from the department to re-engineer the business process. The following study groups are appointed in accordance with this directive:
It is.
(1) The following Study Group is being appointed for the services of Slum Rehabilitation Authority, Mumbai.
Study Group

para_trans: Government Circular No: Narrow-2024 / No.06 / Administration-4,
(2) For services from the office of the Maharashtra Housing and Area Development Authority (MHADA), study as follows:
A group is being formed.
Study Group
(3) The scope of the study group shall be as follows:
(1) To simplify and streamline the process with a view to facilitate the delivery of notified services to the citizens.
Re-engineering the business process.
(2) Preparation of Common Application Form.
(3) To develop procedures for linking the service to Digi-Locker.
(4) Setting a time limit for the preservation of records in respect of notified services.
(4) The time period for the submission of the report -
The above study groups should submit their report to the government within three months.
(5) The study group may hold meetings as required.
This Government Circular is available on the website of the Government of Maharashtra www.maharashtra.gov.in.
